div.p:
He will probably bring a formal message from the King urging in a general way that you give special attention to the Middle East. If the pattern here follows that in London and Paris, this message will be relatively bland. But it is believed that Laraki has instructions to press orally the following points:
—that further deterioration will lead to further Soviet and radical gains;
—that the U.S. not deliver further arms to Israel;
—that the U.S. press Israel to withdraw from the occupied territories;
—that the U.S. press Israel to accept a political solution based on the UN Security Council resolution.
—that the U.S. press Israel to accept a role for the Palestinians.
